author: CNN
description:
President Trump has given Hamas a Sunday deadline to accept his 20-point peace plan for Gaza. Hamas has agreed to immediate talks on a hostage release, but has stopped short of accepting the full proposal. In response, Israel says it's preparing for the first phase of the ceasefire plan that will possibly end the war.

CNN Jerusalem bureau chief Oren Liebermann reports, and Fredricka Whitfield speaks with Andrew Miller, former deputy Secretary of State for Israeli-Palestinian Affairs in the Biden administration. #CNN #News
title: Israel and Hamas move forward on Trump's Gaza peace plan

author: CNN
description: Russian drones struck two passenger trains in the Sumy region of Ukraine on Saturday.  Officials say one person has died and at least thirty were injured. #russia #drone #strike #train #sumy #ukraine
title: Russian drones strike trains in Ukraine

author: CNN
description:
Adults and children alike were pulled from their Chicago apartments, crying and screaming, during a large overnight raid that has left tenants and neighbors shaken. All were part of a multiagency operation that led to the arrest of 37 undocumented immigrants, most of them from Venezuela but also including people from Mexico, Nigeria and Colombia, a Department of Homeland Security spokesperson told CNN. In the past weeks, federal agents have been deployed on the streets of Chicago and have arrested more than 800 undocumented immigrants since September 8 during what the administration has titled “Operation Midway Blitz,” according to a news release from DHS. Tenants said it appears everyone in the building was detained by federal officers, including US citizens.

In an animated debate, CNN's Abby Phillip discusses with her "Table for Five" panel: podcast co-host Van Lathan, former New Hampshire GOP Congressional candidate Gail Huff Brown, CNN senior political commentator Scott Jennings
title: ICE's Chicago raid: Black Hawk helicopters, flashbangs, kids in zip ties

author: CNN
description:

Senior Editor and Elections Analyst of Cook Political Report David Wasserman discusses the government shutdown and the new definition of "moderate."

 #CNN #News
title: A Dem Senator used to regularly work with the Trump administration. Now he says it's radio silence

author: CNN
description: Department of Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem said on "The Benny Show" she requested the Department of War be deployed to Chicago. Her comments come as DHS released a stylized video of an ICE raid in Chicago and during her visit to an Immigration and Customs Enforcement facility in Broadview, Illinois.
title: Noem says Department of War is coming to Chicago

author: CNN
description:
Amid the continuing government shutdown, a portrait of President Donald Trump may be featured on a commemorative $1 coin issued by the United States Mint in honor of America’s 250th birthday in 2026, according to first drafts of the images confirmed by the US Treasury. It’s not clear the controversial coin design will be minted: It’s against US law to display the image of a sitting president or living former president. A president may be featured on a coin no sooner than two years following the president’s death.

CNN senior White House correspondent Kristen Holmes reports, and Erin Burnett discusses with her "OutFront" panel: "Firing Line" host Margaret Hoover, former CNN senior political analyst John Avlon and former Democratic New York congressman Mondaire Jones. #CNN #News
title: Trump coin revealed amid a shutdown with no end in sight

author: CNN
description:
Palestinians in Gaza have been reacting to Hamas’ partial acceptance of US President Donald Trump’s peace proposal with a mixture of optimism and skepticism as Israel’s government and military are preparing for the first phase of the ceasefire plan and the Gaza death toll passes 67,000 according to the health ministry’s latest figures.  Hamas said it has agreed to “immediately” enter negotiations for the release of all hostages.

#CNN #News #Gaza
title: Palestinians react to Gaza peace plan

author: CNN
description: Sanae Takaichi has been elected to lead Japan’s ruling Liberal Democratic Party, making history as its first female leader. The 64-year-old is on track to become the country’s first female prime minister. CNN’s Hanako Montgomery reports from Tokyo outside the LDP’s headquarters, explaining who Takaichi is and what this means for Japan. #CNN #News #Japan
title: Who is Sanae Takaichi, Japan's likely first female prime minister?

author: CNN
description: James Gibson spent almost 30 years in prison for a double murder he didn’t commit, tortured by police before his wrongful conviction. CNN’s Omar Jimenez was in Chicago when Gibson was awarded nearly $15 million by the city. Listen to “CNN Presents: Tortured Justice with Omar Jimenez” wherever you get your podcasts. #cnn #news #shorts
title: Man wrongfully convicted for double murder awarded nearly $15M

author: CNN
description: A Chicago man reunited with his dog Pete after he went missing 10 years ago. Pete was found in Northwestern Indiana, when animal control picked him up and tracked his microchip back to his owner.
title: Surprise call leads man to reuniting with his dog after 10 years
